            services to maintain the integrity of the appliance and ensure
            accurate diagnostics.
          </p>

          <h3>LG</h3>
          <p>
            LG refrigerators are celebrated for their innovative designs and
            energy efficiency. Repair costs for LG models can vary but
            generally fall within a similar range to other high-tech brands.
            Expect to pay between <b>$200 and $450</b> for common repairs like
            fixing a defective evaporator fan or replacing a damaged door gasket.
            If the problem involves the compressor or other critical cooling
            system components, the cost can escalate to between <b
