            specialized knowledge and parts, so it's advisable to seek out
            authorized repair services to ensure quality repairs and
            preserve warranty conditions.
          </p>

          <h3>GE</h3>
          <p>
            GE refrigerators are a staple in many homes, offering a balance
            of affordability and functionality. Repair costs for GE models
            are typically moderate, with common fixes such as replacing
            thermostats, door seals, or water filters often costing between <b
              >$150 and $350</b
            >. For more intricate repairs, like those involving the
            compressor or electronic control boards, costs can rise to
            between <b>$400 and $700</b>. The availability of parts and the
            widespread presence of GE-certified technicians can help keep
            repair costs reasonable and turnaround times quick, making GE a
            practical choice for many Home.
